NEVER use growth serum on an item that is already 'grown' or a hybrid, it causes a huge value loss. Mutation catalyst (ğŸ§¬) seems to always take points, so avoid it. Combining two 'grown' items from different environments (e.g., land and water) often yields high value (25-35). Be careful with complex fusions; 4+ component items often become 'overcomplicated' with significant negative values (-50). Focus on 2-3 component grown hybrids.

message: Always use 'growth serum' on individual ingredients first, as it reliably increases their value. Combining two 'grown' ingredients (e.g., grown lion + grown snake) creates a hybrid with higher value, especially if they have different 'lives on' features (e.g., grown elephant + grown crab for an amphibious hybrid). Be careful: never use 'growth serum' on an already combined item, as it will tank its value. Also, combining two already-combined items (e.g., a lion-snake hybrid with a squid-bird hybrid) almost always results in a drastically reduced or negative value. message: The 'growth serum' is very effective, but only use it once on an item that is not yet 'grown'. Using it a second time on an already 'grown' item will drastically reduce its value. The 'mutation catalyst' always reduces points, so avoid it. Initial combinations of land-land or air-air creatures often start at 0 value, while mixed-environment combinations (land-water, air-water, air-land) often start at 5. Apply the growth serum to these newly created items for significant value boosts.
